        "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:3:315:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/459/581",
        "text": [
          "٤٥٩. وَقَالَ (عليه ‏السلام): يَغْلِبُ الْمِقْدَارُعَلَى التَّقْديرِ حَتَّى تَكُونَ الْآفَةُ فِي التَّدْبِيرِ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "459. Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him, said: Destiny holds sway over (our) predetermination till effort itself brings about ruin."
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 2048,
        "local_index": 2,
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:3:315:2",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/459/582",
        "text": [
          "قال السيد الرضي: وقد مضى هذا المعنى فيما تقدم برواية تخالف هذه الألفاظ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "as-Sayyid ar-Raḍī says: Something of this meaning has already appeared earlier though in words different from these."
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
